WEBVTT

00:10:28.606 --> 00:10:30.083
How did you account for that --

00:10:30.107 --> 00:10:33.114
was there something special or different
in what you were doing,

00:10:33.138 --> 00:10:34.926
did you just feel great good fortune?

00:10:34.950 --> 00:10:38.093
MH: Well, certainly, I had the opportunity
to be an intern at Ariel

00:10:38.117 --> 00:10:40.714
and I immediately knew
that I was at a special place.

00:10:40.738 --> 00:10:43.425
The founder of our firm
is a gentleman named John Rogers,

00:10:43.449 --> 00:10:46.751
and he was one of these people
who changed my life.

00:10:46.775 --> 00:10:48.791
And he changed my life by telling me,

00:10:48.815 --> 00:10:51.537
like my mother did,
that I could be or do anything.

00:10:51.561 --> 00:10:55.433
And the way John did it, was he said,
the first day I went to work at the firm,

00:10:55.457 --> 00:10:57.704
"You know, Mellody,
you're going to be in rooms

00:10:57.728 --> 00:11:00.395
with people who have big titles
that make a lot of money,